race.comment: HELL BENT (3) produced a modest effort most recently when fifth at Warragul over 460m behind Petit Mamselle (26.56) in a Maiden. Was in the money prior to that. Form from his last run is proving to be solid. Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. DREAM BIG (1) out of the money last few starts but gets his best chance from the cherry. Last time finished 5th on November 11 over 400m at this track behind Potent Crew beaten 9 lengths (23.60) in a Maiden. Leading chance. ROTHWELL BONNIE (6) hit the ground running from out wide and on speed early but faded and swamped late when 5th at this track in Maiden FIN company. Has ability and is one of the better chances. ZIPPING KENTUCKY (8) looks an each-way chance.
